/i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Mautby was born about 1350, in Paston, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 daughter with Aleonore Louvair. He died on 28 April 1418, in his hometown, at the age of 69."},"et":{"abt 1350–28 April 1418":"umbes 1350–28. aprill 1418","1355–Female":"1355–Surnud","1381–1424":"1381–1424","1350–1418":"1350–1418","1424":"1424","1355":"1355","28 April 1418":"28. aprill 1418","abt 1350":"umbes 1350","1350":"1350","1381":"1381","1418":"1418","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Burnham Thorpe, Norfolk, England":"Burnham Thorpe, Norfolk, England"},"fi":{"abt 1350–28 April 1418":"noin 1350–28. huhtikuuta 1418","1355–Female":"1355–Kuollut","1381–1424":"1381–1424","1350–1418":"1350–1418","1424":"1424","1355":"1355","28 April 1418":"28. huhtikuuta 1418","abt 1350":"noin 1350","1350":"1350","1381":"1381","1418":"1418","Paston, Norfolk, England":"Paston, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Burnham Thorpe, Norfolk, England":"Burnham Thorpe, Norfolk, England"},"fr":{"abt 1350–28 April 1418":"environ 1350–28 avril 1418","1355–Female":"1355–Décédée","1381–1424":"1381–1424","1350–1418":"1350–1418","1424":"1424","1355":"1355","28 April 1418":"28 avril 1418","abt 1350":"environ 1350","1350":"1350","1381":"1381","1418":"1418","Paston, Norfolk, England":"P